article.headline: E. Kentucky 92, Tennessee Tech 90, 2OT
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Mike Rose scored 20 points to send Eastern Kentucky to a 92-90 win over Tennessee Tech in double overtime on Saturday night. The Colonels (13-9, 8-6) snapped the Golden Eagles' eight-game winning streak and won their third straight contest. Tech (14-10, 10-5) didn't score its first bucket of the second extra period until the 1:15 mark and made just 13-of-27 free throws. Rose had a clutch steal, forced a turnover and scored Eastern Kentucky's first four points of the second overtime. Rose scored 14 points in the second half. Adam Leonard added 20 points, while Julian Mascoll chipped in with 17 to lead the Colonels. Leonard connected on five of his team's 11 shots from long range. Eastern had possession of the ball in the closing seconds of the first overtime, but Mascoll's basket failed to beat the buzzer. The Colonels led 74-69 with 49 seconds remaining in regulation, but Tech scored the last five points and had a chance to win at the buzzer. Anthony Fisher's 3-pointer from the left wing bounced off the front of the rim. The Golden Eagles held a 37-34 halftime lead, but the Colonels forced 10 ties and nine lead changes in the second half to force overtime. Fisher led the Golden Eagles with 19 points, followed by Belton Rivers with 18. Amadi McKenzie had 16, Francis Kabore scored 12 and Rashaud Nixon chipped in with 10. Fisher and Belton Rivers combined for 21 points in the opening half.
